(Chief Technology Officer -- Position Description) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MANDATE CONTEXT) Tj
T*
(This is a succession mandate: the current CTO is being promoted internally to a group-wide role) Tj
T*
(and a replacement is needed to lead the technology organisation for the core product line.) Tj
T*
(Internal context: the engineering team has grown quickly over the last two years and would) Tj
T*
(benefit from stronger platform and reliability discipline; this should be treated as a priority) Tj
T*
(for the first six months.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(IDEAL PROFILE) Tj
T*
(We need a technically credible, product-minded Chief Technology Officer who has scaled an) Tj
T*
(engineering organisation through a period of rapid growth, and who is equally comfortable in the) Tj
T*
(codebase and in the boardroom.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(REPORTING STRUCTURE) Tj
T*
(The role reports to the Chief Executive Officer. The CTO will have six direct reports and lead) Tj
T*
(an engineering, product, and data organisation of around one hundred and twenty people. The role) Tj
T*
(is based in Amman, Jordan, with regular travel to Dubai.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(EMPLOYMENT AND PACKAGE) Tj
T*
(This is a full-time, permanent position, with a target start date of 1 November 2026. The base) Tj
T*
(salary range is USD 28,000 to USD 35,000 per month. The notice period required is two months.) Tj
T*
(Bonus target is 30 percent of base salary. LTIP: a standard employee stock option grant, vesting) Tj
T*
(over four years.) Tj
T*
(Benefits and allowances include a remote-work stipend, an annual learning and conference budget,) Tj
T*
(and premium health cover for the candidate and their family.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(CANDIDATE REQUIREMENTS) Tj
T*
(Required: experience scaling an engineering organisation from roughly fifty to over one hundred) Tj
T*
(engineers.) Tj
T*
(Required: hands-on experience with platform reliability, on-call practices, and incident) Tj
T*
(management at scale.) Tj
T*
(Preferred: experience introducing applied machine learning or AI features into an existing) Tj
T*
(product.) Tj
T*
(Preferred: prior experience presenting technology strategy directly to a board.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(COMPETENCY WEIGHTING) Tj
T*
(Technically, platform architecture and reliability should carry the most weight, closely) Tj
T*
(followed by engineering management at scale, with data and AI strategy and security and) Tj
T*
(compliance each carrying a somewhat smaller share.) Tj
T*
(Behaviourally, cross-functional influence with product and commercial stakeholders should be) Tj
T*
(weighted most heavily, with team building and mentorship close behind, and resilience under) Tj
T*
(ambiguity weighted a little lower.) Tj
